### Transaction.js uses hardcoded string matching (e.g., if (uri.includes('milkomeda'))) to determine the network for error messages. This is fragile; if a URL changes or a new network is added, the error handling breaks or provides incorrect info.

### Fix: Use the chainId from the config/context to identify the network reliably.

